### Add Collection to RxDB Database with Schema

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/quickstart.html

Shows how to add a new collection to an existing RxDB database. Collections are used for storing and querying data, similar to SQL tables. Each collection requires a JSON schema to define its structure and data types.

```javascript
await myDatabase.addCollections({
  todos: {
    schema: {
      version: 0,
      primaryKey: 'id',
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        id: {
          type: 'string',
          maxLength: 100
        },
        name: {
          type: 'string'
        },
        done: {
          type: 'boolean'
        },
        timestamp: {
          type: 'string',
          format: 'date-time'
        }
      },
      required: ['id', 'name', 'done', 'timestamp']
    }
  }
});
```

