### Define RxDB Collection Schema with Dynamic Data

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/rx-schema.html

This example demonstrates how to define an RxDB collection schema that allows for arbitrary JSON data within a specific field by setting its type to 'object'. This approach is useful when some document fields have an unpredictable structure. RxDB's validation and indexing mechanisms will still apply to other defined fields.

```javascript
{
    "version": 0,
    "primaryKey": "id",
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "id": {
            "type": "string",
            "maxLength": 100
        },
        "myDynamicData": {
            "type": "object"
            // Here you can store any JSON data
            // because it's an open object.
        }
    },
    "required": ["id"]
}
```

