### RxDB Schema for Indexed Embeddings

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/javascript-vector-database.md

Defines a RxDB collection schema for storing embeddings along with pre-calculated index values. The index values are strings with a fixed length to ensure precise sorting in IndexedDB. This schema includes fields for document ID, embedding vectors, and five index fields (idx0-idx4).

```typescript
const indexSchema = {
    type: 'string',
    maxLength: 10
};
const schema = {
    "version": 0,
    "primaryKey": "id",
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "id": {
            "type": "string",
            "maxLength": 100
        },
        "embedding": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
                "type": "number"
            }
        },
        // index fields
        "idx0": indexSchema,
        "idx1": indexSchema,
        "idx2": indexSchema,
        "idx3": indexSchema,
        "idx4": indexSchema
    },
    "required": [
        "id",
        "embedding",
        "idx0",
        "idx1",
        "idx2",
        "idx3",
        "idx4"
    ],
    "indexes": [
        "idx0",
        "idx1",
        "idx2",
        "idx3",
        "idx4"
    ]
}
```

