### RxDB LocalStorage Setup with RxDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-storage-localstorage.md

This snippet demonstrates the basic setup for using RxDB's LocalStorage RxStorage. It includes importing the necessary functions, creating a database instance with LocalStorage as the storage engine, adding a collection with a defined schema, inserting a document, and querying for documents.

```typescript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb/plugins/core';
import { getRxStorageLocalstorage } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-localstorage';

// Create a Database
const db = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'exampledb',
    storage: getRxStorageLocalstorage()
});

// Add a Collection
await db.addCollections({
  tasks: {
    schema: {
      title: 'tasks schema',
      version: 0,
      primaryKey: 'id',
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        id: { type: 'string' },
        title: { type: 'string' },
        done: { type: 'boolean' }
      },
      required: ['id', 'title', 'done']
    }
  }
});

// Insert a document
await db.tasks.insert({ id: 'task-01', title: 'Get started with RxDB' });

// Query documents
const nonDoneTasks = await db.tasks.find({
    selector: {
        done: {
            $eq: false
        }
    }
}).exec();

```

