### Define RxCollection Schema for Key Compression

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/key-compression.md

This snippet illustrates how to define a schema for an RxCollection where key compression is enabled. Setting `keyCompression: true` in the schema instructs RxDB to use compression for this collection's documents. Note the requirement for `maxLength` on the primary key.

```typescript
const mySchema = {
  keyCompression: true, // set this to true, to enable the keyCompression
  version: 0,
  primaryKey: 'id',
  type: 'object',
  properties: {
      id: {
          type: 'string',
          maxLength: 100 // <- the primary key must have set maxLength
      }
      /* ... */
  }
};
// Assuming 'db' is an RxDatabase instance
await db.addCollections({
    docs: {
        schema: mySchema
    }
});
```

