### NoSQL Data Retrieval Across Collections (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/why-nosql.html

This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to retrieve related data from two NoSQL collections ('cities' and 'customers') in an offline-first context. It involves separate queries for each collection and manual linking of results, contrasting with SQL's JOIN functionality.

```javascript
const cityDocument = await db.cities.findOne().where('name').equals('Tokyo').exec();
const customerDocuments = await db.customers.find().where('city_id').equals(cityDocument.id).exec();
```

