### RxDB Schema: Disallow mixed types

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/orga/before-next-major.md

Enforce a stricter schema definition in RxDB by disallowing mixed types for document properties. Currently, a property can accept multiple types (e.g., `['string', 'number']`), which leads to confusion in queries. This change requires each field to have a single, explicit type.

```typescript
interface RxJsonSchema {
    // ... other properties
    properties?: {
        [key: string]: JsonSchema;
    };
}

interface JsonSchema {
    type?: JsonSchemaTypes | JsonSchemaTypes[]; // This should be changed to only JsonSchemaTypes
    // ... other schema properties
}

type JsonSchemaTypes = 'string' | 'number' | 'integer' | 'boolean' | 'array' | 'object' | 'null';

// Example of current problematic schema:
// const schema = {
//     version: 0,
//     title: 'mySchema',
//     properties: {
//         myField: {
//             type: ['string', 'number'] // This should be disallowed
//         }
//     }
// };

// Example of desired schema:
// const schema = {
//     version: 0,
//     title: 'mySchema',
//     properties: {
//         myStringField: {
//             type: 'string'
//         },
//         myNumberField: {
//             type: 'number'
//         }
//     }
// };
```

